  "source_id": "crohns-disease",
  "name": "Crohn's Disease - Fecal Calprotectin Lab Query (Elevated)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find Crohn's patients via elevated fecal calprotectin. Calprotectin is a neutrophil-derived protein elevated in active intestinal inflammation. The clinical cutoff for active IBD is typically >250 mcg/g (some labs use >150). The Synthea module generates calprotectin >500 mcg/g for active Crohn's patients.",
  "prompt": "Find patients with elevated fecal calprotectin lab results greater than 250 micrograms per gram of stool \u2014 the clinical threshold suggesting active inflammatory bowel disease.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with high calprotectin.",
    "broad": "Find patients with elevated fecal calprotectin (a stool marker of intestinal inflammation) \u2014 values greater than 250 mcg/g of stool, suggesting active IBD.",
    "expert": "I need Observation resources with elevated fecal calprotectin. Use LOINC code 38445-3 (Calprotectin [Mass/mass] in Stool). Filter by value-quantity greater than 250 mcg/g. Query: Observation?code=http://loinc.org|38445-3&value-quantity=gt250||ug/g"
  },
